36 16 suam, his own .· emphatic by position ; equivalent to in his case. — innocentiam: the technical word, meaning freedom from the charge of plunder and extortion. In fact, Caesar’s fault lay just the other way, —a lavish and reckless generosity at the expense of subjects or allies. In this sentence, in opposite (chiastic) order, innocentiam is opposed to avaritiam, and felicitatem to male re gesta3 a peculiarly Latin turn.
